This paper focuses on the application of Gradient Boosting Decision Trees (GBDTs) in the federated learning setting, which involves distributed data among multiple parties. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms for learning from data. 

The paper also discusses privacy concerns and security measures, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

The use of locality-sensitive hashing and data transformations indicates that the paper could also fit into cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). 

Finally, the paper's focus on boosting decision trees suggests that it could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which covers topics related to intelligent agents, machine learning, and natural language processing.
